properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 8:15PM CST until February 17 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Light Snow and Icing Possible over Northern Iowa Monday...

.Light snow and a wintry mix of freezing rain and sleet is
forecast to develop over northwest to north central Iowa late
tonight into early Monday, continuing into the late afternoon
hours east of Interstate 35. Snow amounts from 1 to 3 inches are
expected with a light glaze of ice also possible. Winds remain
generally light until the late afternoon hours when some minor
blowing snow may occur.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...North Central and Northwest Iowa

* WHEN...From 3 AM to noon CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could primarily impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO NOON CST MONDAY
